snippet: Rick Santorum’s victories in Minnesota, Colorado and Missouri were his first breakout moments, but how much they will matter in the long run remains unclear.
abstract: Rick Santorum’s victories in Minnesota, Colorado and Missouri are his first breakout moments, but how much they will matter in the long run remains unclear; it is questionable whether he can eclipse immediate rival Newt Gingrich or pose a realistic threat to Mitt Romney, who remains better financed and better organized in other states.
lead_paragraph: Rick Santorum’s victories in Minnesota, Colorado and Missouri were his first breakout moments, but how much they will matter in the long run remains unclear.

headline.seo: Santorum’s Victories May Not Guarantee an Edge
headline.main: A Turn in the Winner’s Circle, With an Uncertain Effect on a Shifting Race
headline.print_headline: A Turn in the Winner’s Circle, With an Uncertain Effect on a Shifting Race
